snippet.textDisplay: Fun fact: if people ever doubt that an idol/idol group is singing live, tell them to listen to the consonants and breaths. Big Hit’s in house recording mics have a higher quality than stage mics. The popping consonants are proof of that. Big Hit’s mics (and their excellent mixing techniques) remove the jarring consonants from the actual single. Also, the harsh breathing is because of their choreo. The breathing is (mostly) removed in their actual songs. This is REAL.
